<h1>Guile HTML Scheme Primer</h1>

You can design custom reports rather easily if you know a bit
of basic html.   And if you know scheme, then the world is at 
your feet, since the report generator uses guile to interpret the
embedded scheme in a report.  You can view the html source for
this example primer by viewing 'primer.ghtml' (probably installed
at <tt>/usr/share/gtt/ghtml/C/primer.ghtml</tt>)
<p>
Some sample scheme expressions, and thier output:

<p>
<ul>
<li> (gtt-hello)  prints the following:
     <?scm  (gtt-hello) ?>
     <br><br>

<li> (gtt-show-project-title)  prints the following:
     <?scm  (gtt-show-project-title) ?>
     <br><br>

<li> (gtt-show-project-desc)  prints the following:
     <?scm  (gtt-show-project-desc) ?>
     <br><br>

<li> (gtt-show-basic-journal)  prints a basic layout of the journal, 
     see journal.ghtml for an example.
     <br><br>

<li> (gtt-show-table)  prints a configurable table showing the 
     journal entries.  See <tt>bigtable.ghtml</tt> for an extended example. 
     <br><br>
     Here's a little example:
     <br><br>
     (gtt-show-table '($memo "blah blah memo" $billable "bulbous blort" $billrate $value "da bucks" $bill_value))
     <br><br>
     will print: <br>
     <?scm (gtt-show-table '($memo "blah blah memo" $billable "bulbous blort" $billrate $value "da bucks" $bill_value)) ?>
     <br><br>

<li> (gtt-show-invoice)  prints a configurable invoice, see 
     <tt>invoice.ghtml</tt> for an example.
     <br><br>

<li> (gtt-show-list '(yabba dabba <i>do</i> (<b>eh duude</b>)))  prints the following:
     <?scm (gtt-show-list '(yabba dabba <i>do</i> (<b>eh duude</b>))) ?>
     <br><br>

<!-- 
<?scm (gtt-show-table '($memo $billable $billrate $task_time $value $bill_value 
$start_datime $stop_datime $elapsed $fuzz))  ?>
-->

</ul>

<p>
Thats all for now folks!

